Pre-Game Insights: Australia and England have played 23 T20Is with the Aussies coming out on top in 10 occasions while England has won 11 of them.
Two matches have ended in a no result.
Australia will be coming into this match after their 39-run win against Oman in their tournament opener.
England's opener was washed out against Scotland.
The pitch at the Kensington Oval in the T20 World Cup 2024 has provided assistance to the fast bowlers and spinners alike, and also to the batters.

Australia's squad includes Mitchell Marsh (c), Ashton Agar, Pat Cummins, Tim David, Nathan Ellis, Cameron Green, Josh Hazlewood, Travis Head, Josh Inglis, Glenn Maxwell, Mitchell Starc, Marcus Stoinis, Matthew Wade, David Warner, Adam Zampa.

England's squad includes Jos Buttler (c), Moeen Ali, Jofra Archer, Jonny Bairstow, Harry Brook, Sam Curran, Ben Duckett, Tom Hartley, Will Jacks, Chris Jordan, Liam Livingstone, Adil Rashid, Phil Salt, Reece Topley, Mark Wood.
